Tbh. I hate low effort conversations.

As a Muslim, I've always felt happier around the Diwali festival. It recalls me of how our neighbours became cheerful and exchanged wishes. My father received numerous gifts on this day, and we anticipated it as if it were our own festival, and our neighbor also honored us. As time passed, I lost my father, and that spark of happiness faded. 
But, regardless of pollution, there is something about the breeze that I continue to miss at each festival. 
Happy Diwali to everyone.

Carry on your father's spark,  rekindle,  spread the light among your loved ones.
